questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application running on the `G1` Garbage Collector experiences a gradual heap memory increase, eventually throwing `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. Analyzing the heap dump shows thousands of `byte[]` instances retained by `java.lang.Thread` objects. The following class is identified as the suspect:

java
@Service
public class PaymentProcessingService {
    private static final ThreadLocal<byte[]> transactionBuffer = new ThreadLocal<>();

    @Async("paymentExecutor")
    @Transactional
    public void processPayment(PaymentRequest request) {
        byte[] buffer = loadSecurityKeys(request);
        transactionBuffer.set(buffer);
        executeVerification(request);
    }

    private byte[] loadSecurityKeys(PaymentRequest r) {
        return new byte[1024 * 1024]; // 1MB
    }
    private void executeVerification(PaymentRequest r) {}
}
